{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_53","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Requirements Drafting and Project Seed Handoff\n     2\t  The `requirements` command family drives idea-to-seed workflows. Draft mode\n     3\t  generates clarifying questions and waits for user answers before proceeding.\n     4\t  Quick mode skips questions entirely. Both modes pass through a draft, review,\n     5\t  and seed generation pipeline, persisting validated payloads, artifacts, and\n     6\t  seed files at durable boundaries.\n     7\t\n     8\t  # RD-001\n     9\t  Scenario: Draft mode generates clarifying questions\n    10\t    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n    11\t    When the user runs \"requirements draft --idea 'Build a REST API'\"\n    12\t    Then a requirements run is created in draft mode\n    13\t    And clarifying questions are generated\n    14\t    And the run transitions to \"awaiting_answers\" status\n    15\t    And an answers.toml template is written to the run directory\n    16\t\n    17\t  # RD-002\n    18\t  Scenario: Draft mode with empty questions skips to completion\n    19\t    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n    20\t    When the user runs \"requirements draft --idea 'Simple change'\"\n    21\t    And the backend returns an empty question set\n    22\t    Then the run continues directly through draft, review, and seed\n    23\t    And the run status is \"completed\"\n    24\t\n    25\t  # RD-003\n    26\t  Scenario: Quick mode skips questions entirely\n    27\t    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n    28\t    When the user runs \"requirements quick --idea 'Build a REST API'\"\n    29\t    Then no question set is generated\n    30\t    And the pipeline proceeds directly to draft, review, and seed\n    31\t    And the run status is \"completed\"\n    32\t    And seed files are written to the run directory\n    33\t\n    34\t  # RD-004\n    35\t  Scenario: Answer submission validates required answers\n    36\t    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status\n    37\t    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n    38\t    Then the TOML answers file is opened in $EDITOR\n    39\t    And answers are validated against the question set\n    40\t    And the pipeline resumes from draft, review, and seed\n    41\t\n    42\t  # RD-005\n    43\t  Scenario: Show displays run state\n    44\t    Given a completed requirements run\n    45\t    When the user runs \"requirements show <run-id>\"\n    46\t    Then the run status, mode, and seed path are displayed\n    47\t\n    48\t  # RD-006\n    49\t  Scenario: Review rejection fails the run\n    50\t    Given a requirements run in progress\n    51\t    When the review stage returns \"request_changes\" outcome\n    52\t    Then the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n    53\t    And the review payload and artifact are still persisted\n    54\t\n    55\t  # RD-007\n    56\t  Scenario: Seed rollback on prompt write failure\n    57\t    Given a requirements run that reached seed generation\n    58\t    When the seed prompt.md write fails after project.json succeeds\n    59\t    Then both seed files are removed via rollback\n    60\t    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n    61\t\n    62\t  # RD-008\n    63\t  Scenario: Contract validation rejects duplicate question IDs\n    64\t    Given a question set payload with duplicate question IDs\n    65\t    When the payload is validated through the question_set contract\n    66\t    Then a domain validation error is returned\n    67\t\n    68\t  # RD-009\n    69\t  Scenario: Contract validation rejects non-approval outcome without findings\n    70\t    Given a review payload with \"rejected\" outcome and empty findings\n    71\t    When the payload is validated through the requirements_review contract\n    72\t    Then a domain validation error is returned\n    73\t\n    74\t  # RD-010\n    75\t  Scenario: Failed run can be resumed via answer\n    76\t    Given a requirements run in \"failed\" status with a committed question set\n    77\t    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n    78\t    Then the pipeline resumes from the answer boundary\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
