{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_103","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Conditional approval semantics**: `conditionally_approved` reviews can complete without any follow-ups, so the run can reach completion without recording the required conditions.\n   - Current: [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs#L170) only rejects non-approval outcomes with empty `findings`; [service.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs#L563) treats an empty `follow_ups` list as valid and proceeds to seed generation/completion.\n   - Expected: Reject `conditionally_approved` review payloads that do not contain at least one follow-up, or otherwise guarantee a non-empty canonical follow-up list before completion.\n   - Reference: Loop 10 acceptance criterion for review outcomes: `conditionally_approved` must complete while recording follow-ups in canonical seed metadata and the rendered handoff summary.\n\n2. **`requirements answer` durable-boundary gating**: the resume gate still trusts `run.json` too much when a partial failure happens after `answers_submitted` is durably journaled.\n   - Current: [service.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs#L336) accepts any `awaiting_answers` run without consulting the journal, but [service.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs#L382) appends `AnswersSubmitted` before [service.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs#L403) persists the run transition. If that later `write_run()` fails, the latest durable boundary is already past the question set, yet a second `requirements answer` call is still accepted.\n   - Expected: Gate resumability from the latest durable boundary for both `awaiting_answers` and `failed` runs, or reorder the transition so `AnswersSubmitted` cannot be committed while the run still appears resumable from the question boundary.\n   - Reference: Loop 10 acceptance criteria for `requirements answer <run-id>` and the durable-boundary invariant.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add a happy-path CLI test for `requirements answer`; current CLI coverage only exercises the nonexistent-run failure path in [tests/cli.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs#L2950).\n2. Replace placeholder workflow stage IDs in requirements contract errors with a domain-neutral identifier; requirements validation failures currently report `planning`, e.g. [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs#L102) and [contracts.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs#L173)."}}
