{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_56","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/010-requirements-drafting-and-project-seed-handoff/20260312193814-spec.md | sed -n '34,70p'\"","aggregated_output":"    34\t- [ ] Requirements drafting reuses `agent_execution`, but `agent_execution` must be generalized from workflow-only `StageContract` usage to a domain-neutral structured-contract interface so requirements contracts do not have to be added to the project workflow `StageId` enum.\n    35\t- [ ] Planner defaults drive question generation, drafting, and project-seed generation; reviewer defaults drive requirements review; existing workspace default backend/model resolution and raw-output persistence rules continue to apply.\n    36\t- [ ] Review outcomes have distinct semantics: `approved` allows seed generation and completion; `conditionally_approved` still completes but records follow-ups in canonical seed metadata and the rendered handoff summary; `request_changes` and `rejected` fail the run after the review payload/artifact are durably committed and before any seed files become visible.\n    37\t- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if the question payload/artifact pair fails to persist, the run must not transition to `awaiting_answers` and no partial question/template files may remain visible.\n    38\t- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if answer validation fails, `answers.json` is not replaced, no draft/review/seed stage runs, and the run remains at the same committed question boundary.\n    39\t- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if the draft or review payload/artifact pair fails to persist, the corresponding journal success event is not appended and no downstream stage begins.\n    40\t- [ ] State invariants for partial failure are explicit: if `seed/project.json` is written but `seed/prompt.md` fails, both seed outputs are removed, the run remains non-completed, and only the already committed draft/review history survives.\n    41\t- [ ] Completed requirements runs are immutable, failed runs retain the latest committed question set, answers, draft, and review artifacts, and `question_round` is monotonic across repeated answer cycles.\n    42\t- [ ] `requirements show <run-id>` prints a suggested `ralph-burning project create --id ... --name ... --flow ... --prompt <seed/prompt.md>` command assembled from `seed/project.json` and `seed/prompt.md`.\n    43\t- [ ] This loop does not auto-create, mutate, select, or delete projects; project handoff is durable seed output only, leaving `project create` as an explicit user action.\n    44\t- [ ] Public behavior is covered by new Gherkin scenarios for: draft requiring answers, draft with no questions, quick-mode happy path, editor failure, answer validation failure, conditional approval handoff, review request_changes failure, and seed-write rollback.\n    45\t- [ ] Existing workspace, project, and run behavior remains unchanged, including the current quick_dev run-execution deferral outside the `requirements` command surface.\n    46\t\n    47\t## Files to Modify/Create\n    48\t- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/mod.rs` - replace the placeholder with module exports and public entrypoints for the requirements lifecycle\n    49\t- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/model.rs` - add requirements run IDs, status enums, journal event types, pointers to latest payloads, and seed metadata\n    50\t- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs` - define domain-neutral contracts for `question_set`, `requirements_draft`, `requirements_review`, and `project_seed`\n    51\t- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/renderers.rs` - render deterministic `questions.md`, `requirements.md`, `review.md`, and seed handoff artifacts\n    52\t- `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs` - orchestrate `draft`, `quick`, `show`, and `answer`, including answer-template validation and seed rollback rules\n    53\t- `src/contexts/agent_execution/model.rs` - generalize invocation metadata away from workflow-only `StageContract` coupling\n    54\t- `src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs` - support domain-neutral contract evaluation while preserving existing workflow behavior\n    55\t- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/contracts.rs` - adapt existing workflow stage contracts to the generalized agent-execution contract interface\n    56\t- `src/adapters/fs.rs` - add filesystem stores for requirements runs, journals, answer files, payload/artifact history, runtime diagnostics, and atomic seed-pair writes\n    57\t- `src/adapters/stub_backend.rs` - add deterministic requirements-stage payloads for tests\n    58\t- `src/cli/requirements.rs` - implement all four requirements commands and the editor-driven answer flow\n    59\t- `src/shared/error.rs` - add invalid requirements state, answer validation, and seed persistence error variants\n    60\t- `tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature` - add public requirements-drafting scenarios\n    61\t- `tests/unit/requirements_drafting_test.rs` - add domain and service tests for the requirements state machine and failure invariants\n    62\t- `tests/cli.rs` - add end-to-end CLI coverage for `requirements draft`, `requirements quick`, `requirements show`, and `requirements answer`\n    63\t\n    64\t## Dependencies\n    65\t- Requires: Loop 9 (Docs Change and CI Improvement Flow Execution)\n    66\t- Blocks: Loop 11 (Daemon routing, tasks, leases, watchers, rebase, and interactive requirements path)\n    67\t\n    68\t---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
